22#include <sys/cdefs.h>
23#ifndef lint
24__RCSID("$NetBSD: print-ipcomp.c,v 1.6 2017/02/05 04:05:05 spz Exp $");
25#endif
26
27/* \summary: IP Payload Compression Protocol (IPComp) printer */
28
29#ifdef HAVE_CONFIG_H
30#include "config.h"
31#endif
32
33#include <netdissect-stdinc.h>
34
35struct ipcomp {
36 uint8_t comp_nxt; /* Next Header */
37 uint8_t comp_flags; /* Length of data, in 32bit */
38 uint16_t comp_cpi; /* Compression parameter index */
39};
40
41#include "netdissect.h"
42#include "extract.h"
43
44void
45ipcomp_print(netdissect_options *ndo, register const u_char *bp)
46{
47 register const struct ipcomp *ipcomp;
48 uint16_t cpi;
49
50 ipcomp = (const struct ipcomp *)bp;
51 ND_TCHECK(*ipcomp);
52 cpi = EXTRACT_16BITS(&ipcomp->comp_cpi);
53
54 ND_PRINT((ndo, "IPComp(cpi=0x%04x)", cpi));
55
56 /*
57 * XXX - based on the CPI, we could decompress the packet here.
58 * Packet buffer management is a headache (if we decompress,
59 * packet will become larger).
60 *
61 * We would decompress the packet and then call a routine that,
62 * based on ipcomp->comp_nxt, dissects the decompressed data.
63 *
64 * Until we do that, however, we just return -1, so that
65 * the loop that processes "protocol"/"next header" types
66 * stops - there's nothing more it can do with a compressed
67 * payload.
68 */
69 return;
70
71trunc:
72 ND_PRINT((ndo, "[|IPCOMP]"));
73 return;
74}
